            <div class="nr-item-body">
              <div class="nr-item-tags"><span class="nr-topic">Ingestion</span></div>
              <h3 class="nr-item-title"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1177/000348949310201008" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hair Relaxer Ingestion: A New Trend</a></h3>
              <p class="nr-item-meta">Muntz, Forsen · Annals of Otology Rhinology & Laryngology · January 1993</p>
              <p class="nr-item-abstract">An early case report published in a major otolaryngology journal documenting what the authors described as a "new trend" of hair relaxer ingestion injuries, primarily in children. The paper details the severe corrosive damage caused by lye-based relaxer formulations to the upper airway and gastrointestinal tract, raising early questions about product safety that remain relevant today.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="nr-item-end"><span class="nr-type-badge nr-type-badge--academic">Academic</span><a href="https://doi.org/10.1177/000348949310201008" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="nr-item-link" aria-label="Open resource">↗</a></div>
